namedLocations.description: Brooklyn (/ˈbrʊklɪn/) is the most populous borough of New York City, with an estimated 2,648,771 residents in 2017. Named after the Dutch village of Breukelen, it borders the borough of Queens at the western end of Long Island. Brooklyn has several bridge and tunnel connections to the borough of Manhattan across the East River, and the Verrazzano-Narrows Bridge connects it with Staten Island. Since 1896, Brooklyn has been coterminous with Kings County, the most populous county in the U.S. state of New York and the second-most densely populated county in the United States, after New York County (which is coextensive with the borough of Manhattan).

namedLocations.description: New Jersey is a state in the Mid-Atlantic region of the United States. It is a peninsula, bordered on the north and east by the state of New York; on the east, southeast, and south by the Atlantic Ocean; on the west by the Delaware River and Pennsylvania; and on the southwest by the Delaware Bay and Delaware. New Jersey is the fourth-smallest state by area but the 11th-most populous, with 9 million residents as of 2017, making it the most densely populated of the 50 U.S. states with its biggest city being Newark. New Jersey lies completely within the combined statistical areas of New York City and Philadelphia. New Jersey was the second-wealthiest U.S. state by median household income as of 2017.

transcript.text: Hello welcome to on print shop.
This video is about virtual block templates.
In this video we will see how to create virtual blocks.
So we are considering that you have already watched the video of how to create PDF block template.
So what does virtual block means?
Like once you have created the PDF block template in Adobe Acrobat, so the created block, the single created block we can split into two or more parts virtually.
Then it helps the virtual block helps in alignment, horizontal alignment as well.
And the syntax of virtual block is curly braces, straight line, straight line and curly braces.
So that's it.
Now let us see how to create virtual block.
So we are just going into the.
So here is the example which we have created last in last video, this template where there is a name, this one is the designation.
Then here you can see there are three things, city, state and zip code.
So we have just taken all these three things into one single block.
But generally if you want to create it or if you want to split it into three parts, then there is a phone.
So you can see there is a phone text dimension, then there is a phone number, facts and cell.
So what we are going to do, we are going to create virtual blocks and will split it in all these blocks into different different blocks.
So for that just go in admin, just go to the templates PDF block template.
And here is the our template which we have imported click on action go to the manage blocks.
So here you can see all the virtual blocks.
So just suppose we have to create virtual blocks for this city, state and zip code.
So I have already shown you the syntax.
So what we will do, we will just take it as a curly braces, straight line then straight line and curly braces.
So this one, this will automatically convert into one virtual block.
Same way we will create it for state.
This one and in the same way we will create it for zip code as well at the end.
So now there is one more thing.
Let's say if we will create the same name of the virtual block.
So it might get confused like what to put.
So instead of this Brooklyn, what we can do?
We can put it as a city.
So our block name will be very clear.
Then we can change it to the state and we can change this to zip code.
OK, as we will click on save button, these three blocks will be aligned over here with the different three different blocks.
Let's say if I click on save button, as I will click on save button, you will be able to see three different blocks.
So here we have created this one.
And here you can see city, state and zip.
So here it was Brooklyn, then it was NJ and it was 38596.
As you will do this, just click on save button.
So here you can see Brooklyn, NJ and 3895.
Now if you go at front store and refresh this page.
So here you can see Brooklyn, NY and NJ.
So here is the Brooklyn, then New York and the code.
So here you can easily create the three different blocks with the you can easily convert 1 single block into three different blocks in the same way.
You just need to create the phone one, fax one and cell one.
Also there is one more thing.
Let's say if someone is not filling any leaving any field, let's say if the fun person is not filling the zip code field.
So it will automatically align horizontally.
So you don't need to align it manually.
So wherever there is a space blank that the previous or next text will take place automatically.
If you have any queries and concerns regarding this video, please connect with us at support at on printshop.com.
Thank you.
